== Mudball exit module ==

The exit module is for:

* declaring possible exit error levels
* exiting with particular error levels

=== mud_define_exit() ===

This will declare a particular error level. Error levels are identified by name and are allocated
a code. The names are constant but the codes can change between software versions.

=== mud_abort() ===

This will exit our process, call it if it's unsafe to continue processing.

=== mud_exit() ===

This will exit the current process for the nominated reason.
